        <div class="text-top-div">
          <div class="markdown"><span><p>Three regression algorithms were evaluated: Linear Regression, Random Forest Regressor, and Gradient Boosting Regressor. Linear Regression achieved the highest R² score of 0.659, outperforming both Gradient Boosting (0.618) and Random Forest (0.571). This suggests that the relationship between housing characteristics and house prices in the dataset is largely linear. While ensemble methods are often more powerful, they did not provide additional predictive benefits for this particular dataset.</p></span></div>
