<p>Seven regression algorithms were evaluated to identify the most suitable model for house price prediction. Linear Regression achieved the highest R² score of 0.659, followed closely by XGBoost (0.646) and Gradient Boosting Regressor (0.618). Despite the availability of more advanced ensemble methods, Linear Regression delivered the strongest predictive performance on this dataset, indicating that the relationship between housing features and house prices is largely linear. The comparison demonstrates that increasing model complexity does not always result in better performance, and model selection should be based on objective evaluation metrics rather than algorithm popularity.</p></span></div>
