<p>To improve model transparency, SHAP (SHapley Additive Explanations) was used to understand how individual features influence house price predictions.</p>
<p>The SHAP analysis identified area as the most influential feature, followed by total_rooms, area_per_room, air conditioning availability, bathrooms, and preferred area status. Higher values of area and total_rooms generally contributed positively toward predicted house prices, while lower values reduced the predicted price.</p>
<p>This analysis provides an interpretable view of model behavior and helps translate machine learning predictions into actionable business insights for real estate decision-making.</p></span></div>
